author: Donna Rachel Edmunds
description: European Union leaders plan to move forward with the creation of an EU military headquarters within the next few days
title: EU Combined Military HQ To Be Launched 'Within Days'

author: BBC News
description: The European Union's Brexit negotiator says no deal is not an option in talks due to start on 19 June.
title: EU's Barnier refuses to imagine UK Brexit talks walkout

description: Marine Le Pen is to abandon all plans to leave the European Union and restore the French franc, accepting that her high-risk strategy has proved a costly error for the party.
title: Marine Le Pen abandons Frexit crusade 'error'

description: Britain has “no time to waste” in Brexit talks, Theresa May will warn as she says formal negotiations about leaving the European Union will start just 11 days after the election.
title: 'No time to waste' as Brexit talks will start just 11 days after the election, says Theresa May

author: William James
description: British Prime Minister Theresa May will on Monday urge voters to back her to deliver the country's exit from the European Union, playing one of her strongest cards in the election campaign as opinion polls show that her party's large lead has shrunk.
title: No time for Brexit delays, says UK's May as poll lead slips

author: Ben Chu
description: Brexit can be an "opportunity" for the eurozone's financial system, France's new finance minister, Bruno Le Maire, has said. Mr Le Maire, who was appointed by the new French President Emmanuel Macron last week, was speaking at a joint press conference in Berlin with his German counterpart Wolfgang Schauble. European politicians have been hoping to force the relocation of the lucrative business of clearing euro-denominated derivatives out of the City of London and into the European Union after Britain leaves the bloc in 2019.
title: A French finance minister says Brexit is an 'opportunity' for the eurozone financial sector

author: Ashley Cowburn
description: Jeremy Corbyn, the Labour leader, has said if he wins the general election his administration would deliver a “fair” immigration policy but refused to be drawn on whether he would bring down the numbers coming into the country. Speaking on Sky News’s Sophy Ridge on Sunday, Mr Corbyn repeated his stance that the free movement of people “obviously ends” when Britain exits the European Union “because it’s a condition of the membership”.
title: Jeremy Corbyn says that immigration policy would be fair, but refuses to say what that means

author: Ian Johnston
description: Theresa May is to warn that the consequences of failing to get the right Brexit deal will be “dire” for ordinary working people. In a speech in Wales, the Prime Minister will seek to persuade voters that she should lead the negotiations with the European Union, rather than Jeremy Corbyn. According to an advance copy of her remarks, she will make clear how quickly the process will start to move after the election on 8 June.
title: May to warn Brexit could have 'dire consequences' for ordinary people
